. IV, 2, 268</bibl>.<lb />2) instruction, acquirement: <cit><quote>of this book this l. mayst thou taste,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 77.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 77, 4</bibl></cit>. <emph>how to forget that l.</emph> (viz to write fair) <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 35</bibl>. <cit><quote>puts to him all the --s that his time could make him the receiver of,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 43</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the court's a l. place,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls I, 1, 191</bibl></cit>.
